tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE experiments (
  experiment_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  nanoparticle_id UUID,
  cell_line TEXT,
  uptake_percentage FLOAT,
  conditions TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE nano_particles_experiments (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_date DATE,
  nano_particle_size FLOAT,
  cell_type VARCHAR(50),
  uptake_percentage FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE analysis_results (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_id INT,
  analysis_date DATE,
  analysis_method VARCHAR(100),
  result_description TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE experiments (
  experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  experiment_date DATE,
  nanoparticle_type VARCHAR(255),
  cell_line VARCHAR(255),
  uptake_percentage FLOAT
);

CREATE TABLE results (
    result_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_id UUID REFERENCES experiments(experiment_id),
    participant_id UUID REFERENCES participants(participant_id),
    uptake_percentage FLOAT NOT NULL,
    result_date DATE NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE experiments (
    experiment_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    experiment_date DATE,
    nanoparticle_id INT,
    cell_type VARCHAR(255),
    uptake_result FLOAT
);
